radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is abnormal with a hyperemic wall and dilated to 11mm and fluid filled. Mild inflammatory stranding is noted in the adjacent fat. No periappendiceal fluid collections are present. Lung bases and cardiac apex are normal. Liver, spleen, gallbladder, pancreas, and bilateral adrenal glands are all normal. Bilateral kidneys are unremarkable. The small and large bowel are normal in course and caliber. There is no abdominal free fluid or free intraperitoneal air. Bladder and prostate are normal. No abnormal lymphadenopathy. No suspicious bony lesions are present.
